      • fromSigningKey

        public static Session fromSigningKey(@NonNull
                                     @NonNull java.lang.String signingKey,
                                     @NonNull
                                     @NonNull java.lang.String apiKeyName,
                                     @NonNull
                                     @NonNull java.lang.String identityId,
                                     @NonNull
                                     @NonNull java.time.Duration tokenDuration)
                              throws com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTCreationException,
                                     java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Utility function to create a new Session from a Signing Key. This function is to be used for server-to-server calls only. The signing key should never be shared with the clients.
        Parameters:
        signingKey - The session signing key configured in Satori.
        apiKeyName - The api key name to be used in the token. This has to be an existing value configured in the Satori dashboard.
        identityId - The user identity id for the session.
        tokenDuration - The duration of the validity of the session.
        Throws:
        com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTCreationException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
